meanings.definition: A genus of harvestmen in the family Gagrellidae.
meanings.english_definition: A genus of harvestmen in the family Gagrellidae.

etymology.value: From Greek 'eu' (good, well) + 'pan' (all) + 'orthos' (straight, upright) + '-us' (standard zoological suffix for genera).

inflection.noun_plural: Eupanorthus (taxonomic names are often treated as singular even when referring to the group)

usage_notes.explanation: Scientific genus name, used in taxonomic classification.
